LDK Solar Said to Plan Sale of Yuan Notes as Soon as Tomorrow

-- B y   S h e l l e y   S m i t h
-- 
2011-02-17T04:33:27Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-17/ldk-solar-said-to-sell-1-5-billion-yuan-of-notes-as-soon-as-tomorrow.html
LDK Solar Co., a Chinese maker of
solar energy products, plans to sell about 1.5 billion yuan of
bonds to be settled in U.S. dollars as soon as tomorrow,
according to a person familiar with the matter.  Citigroup Inc. and Morgan Stanley are managing the sale of
the three-year notes, said the person, who asked not to be
identified because the details are private.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Shelley Smith in Hong Kong at 
 ssmith118@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Hugh Chow at 
 hchow12@bloomberg.net  